I don't have a mnemonic for this but I think if you make a literal translation it should become easy. 

We have visited - nous avons visité (avoir - to have/ to be having)

We are going to visit - nous allons visiter (aller- to go/ to be going)

Also remember that in the futur proche the second verb has to be on infinitive.
